Make sure that you pay attention to what bills you are paying with and count your change! I ordered two of the $2 lattes/cappucinos which came to $4.36. I handed the cashier $5.36 but instead of giving me back change she turned her attention to counting change in the tip jar. I asked for my $1 back which prompted a big argument because of course she said that I had only given her $4. I did not leave my house on a day when the high was 32 degrees outside to come rob you out of $1. I know that I paid with a $5 bill because that was the change that my partner had just gotten from one of the beauty supply stores on Myrtle. Besides, I used cards frequently enough that I almost never have $4 in singles. Nonetheless, she  yells that she'll go check the cameras to check. I asked her to do that and to come back with an apology. Instead she called some guy from the back who said that only the manager could run the tapes. She begrudgingly gave me the change back and I left. Btw, she entered the incorrect amount on the receipt which makes me think that she set out to be deceptive.
